This is the independent track (SPO-triplet pipeline), not the axum codegen
emitter (C1-C3). It's the real unlock for an end-to-end run against
OpenProject's Ruby source.

Structure (refactored the single-file scaffold into modules for file-disjoint
fanout):
  src/lib.rs        extract() + RubyClass (added `columns` field) + module wiring
  src/scan.rs       shared primitives (orchestrator): strip_comment, macro_symbols,
                    def_blocks (Ruby keyword-depth block matcher), ivar_assignments
                    — with 5 unit tests. The keystone the 3 extractors share.
  src/parse.rs      parse_models: walk app/models/*.rb + db/schema.rb -> RubyClass
  src/fields.rs     extract_fields: schema columns + memoized @ivar derived attrs
  src/functions.rs  extract_functions: def bodies (reads/raises/traverses) +
                    synthetic _validate guard for declarative validations
  tests/ruby_extract_test.rs + tests/fixtures/openproject/  the end-to-end spec

Fanout: Phase 0 (orchestrator, heavy): scan.rs (verified, 5 unit tests) +
        fixtures + integration test + lib.rs restructure. Phase 1: 4 agents
        file-disjoint (parse, fields, functions, RUBY-FRONTEND.md). 0 fanout
        fix-loop iterations — integration test passed first try after wiring.

Decision: line-based scanner, NOT lib-ruby-parser. Reasons: crate Cargo.toml
        explicitly values "zero external parser deps so the target shape can be
        locked first"; avoids registry/offline risk; Rails models are regular
        enough for the standard subset. Honest gap list (heredocs, metaprogramming,
        multi-line chains, concerns, scope lambdas) documented in RUBY-FRONTEND.md.

Policy: PR-driven, no patches in calibration/. Deliverable = vendor/ mirror +
        docs/SPRINT_C4_REPORT.md. One sprint = one commit.
